        "title": "See also"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "emphasis",
                "text": "sqrt"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " has--consistent with common convention--as its branch cut the\nreal \"interval\" ["
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "-inf"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": ", 0), and is continuous from above on it.\nA branch cut is a curve in the complex plane across which a given\ncomplex function fails to be continuous."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Notes"
      },
